        #aboutme.panel.panel-info
          #aboutme-title-wrp.panel-heading
            h3#aboutme-title.panel-title
              | About me
          #aboutme-content.panel-body
            p
              | I'm both a
              span.text-info student
              | and a
              span.text-info scholar
              | with immense interest in studying and
              span.text-warning
                | understanding things in low-level details
              | .
            p
              | The strange thing is I consider myself an
              span.text-info holist
              | but I also love to go in deep in things.
            p
              span.text-warning
                | Abstraction levels are so fucking important
              span.text-muted
                | and those engineers ignoring them should burn in the hell.
            p
              | Mastering an abstraction level typically involves breaking it.
              br
              | This is what I consider myself strong.
              span.text-warning
                | Take a thing and analyze it.
                | Then, try to understand its behaviour:
              ul
                li What are its limits?
                li What is that thing useful for?
                li When should I use it?
                li
                  | Is it
                  span.text-info extensible
                  |                   /
                  span.text-info modular?
                li
                  | Does it encourage
                  span.text-info reuse
                  | ?
            div
              p
                | I am a hater but I love everything I spend enough time in.
                | If I have choose some hobbies or fields of study, they may be:
              .list-group
                .list-group-item
                  h4.list-group-item-heading.text-info
                    | Divulgative physics
                  .list-group-item-text
                    p
                      | just divulgative because I am too dumb to understand it
                      | from a scientist perspective.
                    p
                      | In another life, maybe, I will study Physics instead of
                      | Computer-Science..
                .list-group-item
                  h4.list-group-item-heading.text-info
                    | Software analysis, design and (less) development
                  .list-group-item-text
                    p
                      | Long life to
                      span.label.label-info
                        | Model-Driven-Development
                      | and GTFO shitty programmers exploiting Agile methodologies
                      | to avoid software design.
                    p
                      | In particular, as an holist I am fascinated by:
                      ul
                        li
                          | Tackling the ackward squad of
                          span.label.label-info
                            | distributed
                          | and
                          span.label.label-info
                            | concurrent
                          | software
                        li
                          | How to design
                          span.label.label-info
                            | expert systems
                    p
                      | But I also like:
                      ul
                        li
                          span.label.label-info
                            | Genetic algorithms
                          | , specially in designing fuzzers..
                        li
                          span.label.label-info
                            | Machine learning
                          | algorithms and models
                .list-group-item
                  h4.list-group-item-heading
                    span.text-info
                      | Ethical
                    | Software and Hardware hacking
                  .list-group-item-text
                    p
                      | Mainly
                      span.label.label-info
                        | reverse engineering
                      |                       and
                      span.label.label-info
                        | binary exploitation
                      | .
                    p
                      | Thanks to
                      a(href='http://smashthestack.org')
                        | SmashTheStack
                      | for their awesome challenges.
                .list-group-item
                  h4.list-group-item-heading
                    span.text-info
                      | I ♥ old-school CLI-based software
                  .list-group-item-text
                    p
                      | These days, CLI is 
                      i really
                      |  under-rated.
                    p
                      | I ♥ the 
                      span.text-info UNIX way
                      | :
                      span.text-warning KISS over Complex
                      | .
                    p
                      | Small stackable blocks with stdin, stdout, stderr and pipe
                      | them!
                      span.label.label-info
                        | Gentoo
                      | +
                      span.label.label-info
                        | Awesome WM
                      | +
                      span.label.label-info
                        | VIm
                      | +
                      span.label.label-info
                        | ZSH
                      | all the way!
                      span.text-muted
                        | and GTFO GUIs.
                    p
                      | I ♥ to configure and fine-tune my (mostly) Gentoo-based
                      | systems.
                    p
                      | I've also created an NON-production-ready
                      | hassle-free software for managing heterogeneous-systems
                      | configurations called
                      a(href='https://github.com/alem0lars/fizzy') Fizzy
                      | encouraging reuse and other common software engineering
